This thing is mostly stocked with history books on medieval stuff. There's a few standouts though, like meditation and...gardening?
Oh, here's one you don't see every day. "How To Live as an Undead - Essential Tips for Making the Most of Your Reanimated Existence". That's...weirdly specific. How does this book even exist?
There's a few of these, actually. "How To Sew Your Arm Back On and other First Aid Tips for Zombies!"..."Making Friends as an Undead Abomination - How I came to Terms with My New Life."
So I guess somewhere, for whatever reason, being a sentient zombie is a common thing? Common enough for these to exist at least??
